1. 'make' is a command used to compile program pieces into a final executable.

2. Having the source code allows programs to remain opensourced. With the source code, people can make changes, develop solutions, and improve
programs overall for the community. It also gives more freedom and safety to the users since users can find and fix issues found in the code. Often,
responcible users will report these issues and make the wider community more safe. 

3. Source code is the code which makes up a program. 

4. Binary is the counting system that computers use. Binary only has two numbers, 1 and 0, which are used to count. This number system is base two.
Computers use binary since it mirrors their internal ON/OFF nature, and binary usually is seen in forms like bytes, which are 8 bits. A bit is a 1 or 0. 
